// ============================================================================
// HRMS Phase 1 — Prisma Schema (REVISED)
// ============================================================================
// This revision folds in the schema critique. Change markers:
//   [T1]       resolved before first migration (expensive to retrofit)
//   [T2]       cheap correctness fix
//   DECISION:  a Tier-3 judgement call made by the lead; override freely
//
// Original design principles still hold (see 04_Data_Model_Phase1.md):
//  1. organizationId on every table — tenant-ready, SaaS is a config flip.
//  2. Payroll/salary data is append-only and versioned — corrections are new
//     rows, not edits.
//  3. statutoryRates is looked up by effectiveDate at calc time — NOT an FK.
//  4. leaveApprovalSteps count is the single/multi-level toggle, not a branch.
//
// [T1-5] Delete policy: default posture is RESTRICT (fail loud — never let a
// delete silently cascade through retention-critical data). Explicit onDelete
// is set below on (a) retention-critical paths (Restrict) and (b) genuinely
// cascade-safe children like sessions/approval steps. A DPA erasure is an
// anonymize-in-place workflow, NOT a row delete — see DECISION on Employee.
// ============================================================================

generator client {
  // Prisma 7: Rust-free client. moduleFormat="cjs" is required so the generated
  // client is CommonJS and interoperates with NestJS's CommonJS runtime.
  provider     = "prisma-client"
  output       = "../src/generated/prisma"
  moduleFormat = "cjs"
}

datasource db {
  // Prisma 7: the connection URL now lives in prisma.config.ts (CLI/migrations)
  // and is passed to the driver adapter at runtime — not declared here.
  provider = "postgresql"
}

